def calculate_distance(my_x,my_y,ind):
    dist=[]
    for ord in range(len(new_centers)):
        if (ord != ind):
            horizontal_dist=(bottom_distance/width)+(abs((top_distance/width)-(bottom_distance/width))*((height-my_x)/height))
            if (abs(my_x-new_centers[ord][1]) >= (height * 2/3)):
                vertical_dist=(my_x - new_centers[ord][1]) * (side_distance/height)
            else:
                if(abs(my_x-new_centers[ord][1]) < (height * 1/3)):
                    if (height-my_x < (height/3)):
                        vertical_dist=(my_x - new_centers[ord][1]) * ((side_distance/height)/2)
                    if (height-my_x > height * 2/3):
                        vertical_dist=(my_x - new_centers[ord][1]) * ((side_distance/height)*2)
                    if (height-my_x <= height * 2/3) & (height-my_x >= height/3):
                        vertical_dist=(my_x-new_centers[ord][1])*((side_distance/height)+((height/2 - my_x+80)/(height*10)))
                else:
                    vertical_dist=(my_x - new_centers[ord][1]) * ((side_distance/height)/1.15)
                
            to_center=math.sqrt((vertical_dist) ** 2 + ((my_y - new_centers[ord][0]) * horizontal_dist) ** 2)
            dist.append(to_center)
    return(min(dist))

starting_time = time.time()

img = cv2.imread("ss11.png")
img_map=img.copy()

img_map=np.zeros(img_map.shape, np.uint8)
height, width, channels = img.shape
real_height,real_width=((25/height),(15/width))
bottom_distance,top_distance,side_distance=(8,22,20)

blob = cv2.dnn.blobFromImage(img, 0.00392, (416, 416), (0, 0, 0), True, crop=False)
net.setInput(blob)
outs = net.forward(output_layers)

class_ids = []
confidences = []
boxes = []
centers=[]
distances=[]


for out in outs:
    for detection in out:
        scores = detection[5:]
        class_id = np.argmax(scores)
        if class_id==0:
            confidence = scores[class_id]
            if confidence > 0.5:
                # Object detected
                center_x = int(detection[0] * width)
                center_y = int(detection[1] * height)
                w = int(detection[2] * width)
                h = int(detection[3] * height)
                # Rectangle coordinates
                x = int(center_x - w / 2)
                y = int(center_y - h / 2)
                boxes.append([x, y, w, h])
                confidences.append(float(confidence))
                class_ids.append(class_id)
                centers.append([center_x,center_y])
            
            
indexes = cv2.dnn.NMSBoxes(boxes, confidences, 0.5, 0.4)
font = cv2.FONT_HERSHEY_PLAIN

new_centers=[]
new_boxes=[]
new_classes=[]
for j in range(len(boxes)):
    if j in indexes:
        new_centers.append(centers[j])
        new_boxes.append(boxes[j])
        new_classes.append(class_ids[j])


    
    

if (len(new_centers) > 1): 
    for j in range(len(new_centers)):
        distances.append(calculate_distance(new_centers[j][1],new_centers[j][0],j))



for i in range(len(new_boxes)):
    x, y, w, h = new_boxes[i]
    label = str(classes[new_classes[i]])
    color = colors[new_classes[i]]
    if new_classes[i]==0:
        cv2.circle(img_map,(new_centers[i][0],new_centers[i][1]),10,(0,255,0))
    else:
        cv2.circle(img_map,(new_centers[i][0],new_centers[i][1]),10,(255,0,0))
        
    cv2.rectangle(img, (x, y), (x + w, y + h), color, 2)
    cv2.putText(img, label, (x, y ), font, 1, color, 2)
    if (len(new_centers) > 1):
        cv2.putText(img, str(round(distances[i], 2)), (x, y+40 ), font, 1, color, 2)
        if distances[i]< 3:
            cv2.circle(img_map,(new_centers[i][0],new_centers[i][1]),2,(0,0,255),10)
    
#cv2.imshow("Image", img)
#cv2.imshow("Map", img_map)
print(round((time.time()-starting_time),2))

import cv2
import numpy as np
import math
import time
# Load Yolo
net = cv2.dnn.readNet("yolov3.weights", "yolov3.cfg")
classes = []

with open("coco.names", "r") as f:
    classes = [line.strip() for line in f.readlines()]
layer_names = net.getLayerNames()
output_layers = [layer_names[i[0] - 1] for i in net.getUnconnectedOutLayers()]
colors = np.random.uniform(0, 255, size=(len(classes), 3))
bottom_distance,top_distance,side_distance=(8,22,20)


# Loading camera
cap = cv2.VideoCapture(0)
font = cv2.FONT_HERSHEY_PLAIN


starting_time = time.time()
frame_id = 0


def calculate_distance(my_x,my_y,ind):
    dist=[]
    for ord in range(len(new_centers)):
        if (ord != ind):
            horizontal_dist=(bottom_distance/width)+(abs((top_distance/width)-(bottom_distance/width))*((height-my_x)/height))
            if (abs(my_x-new_centers[ord][1]) >= (height * 2/3)):
                vertical_dist=(my_x - new_centers[ord][1]) * (side_distance/height)
            else:
                if(abs(my_x-new_centers[ord][1]) < (height * 1/3)):
                    if (height-my_x < (height/3)):
                        vertical_dist=(my_x - new_centers[ord][1]) * ((side_distance/height)/2)
                    if (height-my_x > height * 2/3):
                        vertical_dist=(my_x - new_centers[ord][1]) * ((side_distance/height)*2)
                    if (height-my_x <= height * 2/3) & (height-my_x >= height/3):
                        vertical_dist=(my_x-new_centers[ord][1])*((side_distance/height)+((height/2 - my_x+80)/(height*10)))
                else:
                    vertical_dist=(my_x - new_centers[ord][1]) * ((side_distance/height)/1.15)
                
            to_center=math.sqrt((vertical_dist) ** 2 + ((my_y - new_centers[ord][0]) * horizontal_dist) ** 2)
            dist.append(to_center)
    return(min(dist))




all_points=[]


while True:
    _, frame = cap.read()
    img_map=frame.copy()
    img_map=np.zeros(frame.shape, np.uint8)
    frame_id += 1
    height, width, channels = frame.shape
        # Detecting objects
    blob = cv2.dnn.blobFromImage(frame, 0.00392, (360,360), (0, 0, 0), True, crop=False)
    net.setInput(blob)
    outs = net.forward(output_layers)
    # Showing informations on the screen
    class_ids = []
    confidences = []
    boxes = []
    centers=[]
    distances=[]
    for out in outs:
        for detection in out:
            scores = detection[5:]
            class_id = np.argmax(scores)
            if class_id == 0:    
                confidence = scores[class_id]
                if confidence > 0.55:
                # People detected
                    center_x = int(detection[0] * width)
                    center_y = int(detection[1] * height)
                    w = int(detection[2] * width)
                    h = int(detection[3] * height)
                    # Rectangle coordinates
                    x = int(center_x - w / 2)
                    y = int(center_y - h / 2)
                    boxes.append([x, y, w, h])
                    centers.append([center_x,center_y])
                    confidences.append(float(confidence))
                    class_ids.append(class_id)
    
        
    indexes = cv2.dnn.NMSBoxes(boxes, confidences, 0.4, 0.3) #(boxes, confidences, 0.4, 0.3)
    new_centers=[]
    new_boxes=[]
    new_classes=[]
    for j in range(len(boxes)):
        if j in indexes:
            new_centers.append(centers[j])
            new_boxes.append(boxes[j])
            all_points.append(centers[j])
            new_classes.append(class_ids[j])
            
    if (len(new_centers) > 1): 
        for j in range(len(new_centers)):
            distances.append(calculate_distance(new_centers[j][1],new_centers[j][0],j))
        
        
    for i in range(len(new_boxes)):
        x, y, w, h = new_boxes[i]
        label = str(classes[new_classes[i]])
        color = colors[new_classes[i]]
        if new_classes[i]==0:
            cv2.circle(img_map,(new_centers[i][0],new_centers[i][1]),9,(0,255,0))
        else:
            cv2.circle(img_map,(new_centers[i][0],new_centers[i][1]),9,(255,0,0))
       
        cv2.rectangle(frame, (x, y), (x + w, y + h), color, 2)
        cv2.putText(frame, label, (x, y ), font, 1, color, 2)
        if (len(new_centers) > 1):
            cv2.putText(frame,label + " " + str(round(distances[i], 2)), (x, y), font, 1, color, 2)
            if distances[i] < 3:
                cv2.circle(img_map,(new_centers[i][0],new_centers[i][1]),7,(0,0,255),-1)

    elapsed_time = time.time() - starting_time
    fps = frame_id / elapsed_time
    cv2.putText(frame, "FPS: " + str(round(fps, 2)), (10, 50), font, 3, (80, 80,80), 3)
    cv2.imshow("Map", img_map)
    cv2.imshow("Image", frame)
    
    key = cv2.waitKey(1)
    if key == 27:
        break
cap.release()
cv2.destroyAllWindows()
